<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>𝓙𝓪𝓲𝓷𝓪𝓶 𝓥𝓵𝓸𝓰𝓼</title>

    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">

    <style>
        body {
            background: linear-gradient(to right, rgb(24, 45, 52), rgb(24, 45, 52));
            color: white !important;
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
        }

        header {
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
            backdrop-filter: blur(5px);
            padding: 15px;
        }

        .main-container {
            max-width: 1000px;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
            backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
            padding: 40px;
            border-radius: 15px;
            margin-top: 100px !important;
            box-shadow: 0 10px 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
            margin-top: 40px;
        }

        .blog-title {
            color: #ffddb3;
            font-family: Georgia, serif;
        }

        .btn-outline-warning {
            border-color: #ffddb3;
            color: #ffddb3;
        }

        .btn-outline-warning:hover {
            background-color: #ffddb3;
            color: #1a1a1a;
        }

        h4 {
            color: #ffddb3;
        }

        img {
            transition: transform 0.3s ease-in-out;
        }

        img:hover {
            transform: scale(1.03);
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <%- include('../partials/header') %>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Blog Content -->
    <div class="container main-container">
        <div class="text-center ">
            <h1 class="display-5 blog-title">𝓙𝓪𝓲𝓷𝓪𝓶 𝓥𝓵𝓸𝓰𝓼</h1>
        </div>

        <!-- ✅ Full-width Featured Image -->
        <div class="m-5">
            <img src="/<%= viewblog.imgUrl %>" class="img-fluid w-100 rounded shadow" alt="Featured Blog Image"
                style="max-height: 500px; object-fit: cover;">
        </div>

        <div class="row g-4 align-items-center">
            <!-- Blog Image -->
            <div class="col-md-6 text-center">
                <img src="/<%= viewblog.imgUrl %>" class="img-fluid rounded shadow" alt="<%= viewblog.title %>"
                    style="width: 550px; height: 400px;">
            </div>

            <!-- Blog Text -->
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <h2 class="fw-bold blog-title mb-3">
                    <%= viewblog.title %>
                </h2>
                <p>
                    <%= viewblog.content %>
                </p>

                <ul class="list-unstyled">
                    <li><strong>Rating:</strong> ⭐⭐⭐⭐ (4.0/5)</li>
                    <li><strong>Category:</strong> Animation / Adventure / Comedy</li>
                </ul>

                <small class="text-info">
                    Published: <%= new Date(viewblog.publishDateTime).toLocaleString() %>
                </small><br>

                <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mt-3">
                    <div class="btn-group gap-2">
                        <a href="/like-blog/<%= viewblog._id %>" class="btn btn-sm">
                            <i class="fas fa-thumbs-up fs-4" style="color: royalblue;"></i>
                            <strong class="text-light">
                                <%= viewblog.likes %>
                            </strong>
                        </a>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <a href="/" class="btn btn-outline-warning mt-2">← Back to Home</a>
            </div>

            <!-- Divider -->
            <hr class="my-5 text-light">

            <!-- "ON THE BLOG" Section -->
            <div class="text-center mb-4">
                <h1 class="display-5 blog-title">ON THE BLOG</h1>
            </div>

            <div class="row g-4">
                <!-- Blog Paragraph -->
                <div class="col-md-7">
                    <p style="text-align: justify;">
                    <h5>🎬 The Power of Storytelling: Why We Keep Coming Back to the Movies</h5>
                    <br>
                    Movies have a unique ability to transport us into different worlds, allowing us to live
                    countless lives in just a few hours. Whether it’s an emotional drama, a mind-bending thriller,
                    or a heartwarming romance, cinema connects with us on a level that few other mediums can. From
                    the moment the lights dim in the theater, we’re no longer ourselves—we’re explorers of
                    imagination, emotion, and humanity.

                    <br><br>

                    One of the reasons we’re so drawn to films is the emotional resonance they offer. A
                    well-executed scene, delivered with authenticity by a talented actor, can stir feelings we
                    didn’t even know we had. It’s in these moments that we remember how powerful storytelling can
                    be. Films like The Pursuit of Happyness or Forrest Gump remind us that behind every struggle is
                    a deeply human story waiting to be told.

                    <br><br>

                    Beyond entertainment, movies also hold up a mirror to society. Through historical epics, gritty
                    dramas, and even sci-fi, filmmakers often tackle real-world issues—war, inequality, love, loss,
                    and everything in between. Directors like Christopher Nolan, Greta Gerwig, and Bong Joon-ho use
                    the screen not just to entertain, but to educate and provoke thought.

                    <br><br>

                    Visuals and soundscapes play a critical role as well. Cinematography captures beauty in motion,
                    while a well-composed score elevates each scene’s emotion. Think of Hans Zimmer’s pulse-pounding
                    compositions in Inception or the quiet power of silence in A Quiet Place. These elements create
                    a fully immersive experience that stays with us long after the credits roll.

                    <br><br>

                    At the end of the day, what makes movies truly magical is their universality. No matter your
                    background, language, or age, cinema has a way of making you feel seen and heard. From indie
                    gems to blockbuster hits, every film contributes to the ongoing story of who we are—and who we
                    aspire to be.
                    </p>
                </div>

